name: A BIT OF FROTH
description:
a collection of 'FROTH' pages from obscure comic book artist Michael Fikaris. Started in 1991 and continually released until 2011 - this 200 page oversized paperback contains short comic stories from the  self published comic book zine of some local recognition. Does lots of community work with comics and has even sold comics to the National Gallery of Australia.
The National paper called him 'a graphic art guru'

http://www.smh.com.au/photogallery/national/michael-fikaris--graphic-art-guru-20110804-1idus.html

Each issue comes with a bookmark.

Numbered Limited Edition of 200
Perfect bound softcover
Colour covers 
$13

name: DAILIES 1
description:
Dailies is a comic anthology of artists from the southern hemisphere.

Released approximatley every 6 months and printed in Melbourne, Australia - this intensely independant collection of comic strips, illustrations and short stories come together in a sprawling wonderbeast of the human condition. 

Dailies is edited and designed by M P Fikaris as a curated project and aims to showcase a community of passionate comic artists who do this sort of thing  'dailey' .



January 2012   |   64 pages   |   Tabloid paper size   |   8 pages full colour   |   AU $5 

Dailies Issue 1- Includes ;

MP Fikaris/Tim Danko, Civil, Aaron O’Donnell, Tim Molloy, Georg, Marc Pearson, Ha-Ha, Picnick, Shida, Nelio, James Bonnici, Anthony Woodward, Texta Queen, Jerome Bihan, Adi Firth, Rachel Torbett, Dan Reed, Pip Stafford, Mel Roswell, Sam Wallman, Clint Cure, Karl Wills, Rena Littleson, Leigh Rigozzi, The Pox Girls, Mandy Ord, Simon Hanselmann, Michael Hawkins, Tom O’Hern, Jo Waite, Lucy Berglund, Ted McKinley, Cougar Flashy, Anthony Lister, GhostPatrol, Twoone, Baby Guerilla, Athonk, Ben Hutchings, Glenn Smith, Dan Sibley, Psalm, Mitten Fortress Saigon Whisprs Game, Tim Sterling, Phoenix, Michael Managhetti, Benard Caleo, Hamishi, Ed Wakeham, Alec Morten, Lwnski, Heesco, Clayton Noone, Indira Neville, Ero, Toni Dowd, Dan Fikaris, Jase Harper, James James, Carol Wood, Lachlan Conn, Kieran Mangan.






Digital print quality Version of Issue 1 available for your enjoyment here - http://www.silentarmy.org/dailies--2012.html

name: WORKOBOROUS
description:
James James

WORKOBOROUS is the story of an obsolete robot who is rescued by an alcoholic factory worker. When his rescuer gets too drunk to show up for work the next day the robot opts to go in his place. In the factory he realises the never ending pointlessness and horror of working a blue collar job.

24 pages black and white interior, full colour cover, six dollars. A6 landscape.

$6

name: Everyday life can be pretty interesting stuff.
description:
A book printed after a month long set of comic art workshops with Signal here in Melbourne.

5 cartoonists with different specialties of the art run workshops in the city at a studio for young artists under the age of 21.
Artists Included 
Simon Hanselmann
Mandy Ord
Sam Wallman
Stewart Cole
Kieran Mangan
Michael Fikaris


In  5 parts -

'Lets Draw' : 20 pages of drawings from each artist and student present at 5 workshops.

'What's in a Story' : 10 pages regarding scripts, storytelling and more

'Some Comics' ; 20 pages of finished pages from the students 

'Lets Draw More' : collaborative drawings and doodles from the classes. Some new characters and jokes galore!

'Some more comics' : 12 pages of  comic excerpts from the 5 artists
